Hey Everyone!! I have some super exciting news that I have been keeping a secret for a while…
I’m going back to Nicaragua 🇳🇮 😀❤️…and I’m taking some of y’all with me!!!!! 
.
I will be hosting another surf retreat with @stillsaltyescape April 6-12, 2023!!!! I’m soooooo excited about this and can’t wait to go back to one of my favorite places in the world. 
.
I knew for a long time that I always wanted to visit this unique and beautiful country and when I got to go in 2021 it was even more magical than I ever could have dreamed of. This country has the friendliest people, sickest waves, yummiest food and stunning scenery. 
.
For anyone that likes to travel, or surf or just go on a relaxing vacation to somewhere tropical now is your time! With @stillsaltyescape you will have everything covered (except flight and transportation), a place to stay, food, surfing, video analysis, and some fun activities. Use Code: NIQUEMILLER for $50 off! 
.
This retreat is open to everyone and all skill levels. If you are a pro surfer or first timer there will be all types of instruction and waves we will be going to. I also will be there to help guide and give tips. 
.
This retreat has limited spaces so I would recommend signing up asap. Link is in my bio if you want to come! If you have questions or concerns you can send me or @stillsaltyescape a dm!! ❤️
.
Also scroll thru the pics to see just a few amazing moments from my last trip to Nicaragua 🇳🇮 
.

Made it to the finals again for my second time at @singleandunattached_ ❤️🥹
.
Taking home third place 🥉…bittersweet, really wanted to win (who doesn’t) but happy to be in the top 3 against a super talent international field!!! 

Yesterday just wasn’t quite my day, I couldn’t quite get the waves to work for me. Was patient and waited for what I thought were good sets but all mine just fizzled out in the middle instead of connecting to the inside which is were a lot of bonus points could have been made. 
.
Sometimes surf contest come down to luck and who is sitting in the right place at the right time. But at the end of the day I had lots of fun and many positive notes 📝 to take away. I’m proud of my performance especially bouncing back from a poor showing in the semis and grateful to share the lineup with only 3 other insanely talented and inspiring girls @daisysurf @hirokayoshikawa88 @natsumi_taoka 
.
Now time to rest, recharge and get ready for my next comp here in a few days! Thanks again to @singleandunattached_ for inviting me and putting on a wonderful event in La Union! Congrats to @hirokayoshikawa88 for winning. You were ripping the whole comp 🔥. And great job to all the other competitors, everyone did so well! 
.

Wow what a weekend here in Canada 🇨🇦! I ended up placing third 🥉 in the @queenofthepeak contest..very greatful for the result but I still wish I could have done a bit better and find higher scoring waves in the finals like I did in my earlier rounds…it just wasn’t meant to be 🤷🏽‍♀️…
either way it was an absolute pleasure surfing with such a talented group of girls in the finals and amazing job to everyone that competed this whole weekend. 
.
I would also like to say a huge thank you to @pacificsands for hosting me during my time in Tofino!  @pacificsands made everything so seemless and easy for me to focus on my comp. They had me in room where I could easily see the waves while in general their property is located steps away from the beach and a 5min walk to the comp site. They also had very help staff, on-site restaurants and @surfsister surf shack. I couldn’t recommend them enough if your looking for a surf friendly hotel! 
.
Lastly big thank you to all my sponsors and to all the really nice ppl I met they out the contest and Tofino! And to the judges and staff that put on a great event for @queenofthepeak and the “Lucky Logger Invite” 🫶🏽🫶🏽 Hope to see you all again next year!
